After the authorization is revoked, the device will be unbound with your currently logged-in account and the data stored on the server before the device will be cleared; the data stored in the physical device requires you to perform a manual local physical reset and then clear the data. If the device supports it, you can Reset directly on the device or refer to the revoke authorization in the ‘Privacy Policy’ to reset. None of the above data can be restored after cancellation. To reuse the device, you need to bind again and re-authorize.

"After you withdraw your consent, the device will unbind with your currently logged-in account, clear all cached data in this plug-in, and clear the data stored on the server by the device. The data stored locally on the device needs to be deleted by clicking Menu→Settings→Restore Factory Settings on the device side. After withdrawing consent to the privacy policy, we will stop collecting your personal information. Because the provision of this service relies on the collection of necessary personal information, if you withdraw your consent, it will be deemed that you do not agree to manage the walkie-talkie device through this plug-in. If you want to reuse it, you need to authorize and bind again."

Welcome to the Mi PTT! You can manage your Xiaomi Walkie-Talkie, use wireless communication, and view and share locations on this app. We will adhere strictly to the relevant laws & regulations and the Privacy Policy to protect your personal information. In order to provide basic services, you need to be connected to the Internet and allow the following permissions and functions, so that your necessary personal information can be collected.
